| Concern | Fix |
|---|---|
| No security headers | `app.use(require('helmet')())` |
| No rate limiting | `express-rate-limit` on public routes, especially auth |
| `x-powered-by` header leaks framework | `app.disable('x-powered-by')` (or via helmet) |
| CORS wide open by default | Configure `cors` with an explicit origin allowlist |
| Hard-coded port | `app.listen(process.env.PORT || 3000, ...)` |
| PII (`email`) returned unauthenticated | Require auth; return only the minimum necessary fields |
| No request logging / correlation IDs | `pino-http` or `morgan` with request IDs for forensics |
| `listen()` runs on `require()` | Only start the server when run directly: `if (require.main === module) app.listen(...)` — makes the module safely testable |

## 4. Revised Skeleton

