  const token = req.headers.authorization?.replace(/^Bearer\s+/i, '');
  if (!token || !isValidToken(token)) {
    return res.status(401).json({ error: 'Unauthorized' });
  }
  next();
}
app.get('/users', requireAuth, (req, res) => { /* ... */ });
```

Also consider stripping PII (`email`) unless the caller is authorized to see it.

## 6. Input validation scaffolding

**Issue:** No routes currently take input, but when they do you should validate before handler logic runs. Establish the pattern now.

**Fix (using `zod`):**
```js
