const userIdSchema = z.object({
  id: z.coerce.number().int().positive(),
});

app.get('/users/:id', (req, res, next) => {
  const parsed = userIdSchema.safeParse(req.params);
  if (!parsed.success) {
    return res.status(400).json({ error: 'Invalid user id' });
  }
  // ... use parsed.data.id
});
```

Validate `req.params`, `req.query`, and `req.body` — never trust any of them.

## 7. Hard-coded port / no graceful shutdown

**Issue:** Port 3000 is hard-coded; no shutdown handling means in-flight requests get dropped on SIGTERM (common in containerized envs).

